The Police in Benue State have recovered 46 different types of firearms from various locations of the state in furtherance of the directive of the Inspector General of Police (IGP) to mop-up illegal arms in the country. The State Commissioner of Police, Fatai Owoseni, said at a press conference in Makurdi, that the recovered arms consisted of eight AK-47 rifles, four AK-47 magazines, 126 rounds of live ammunitions, five cartridges as well as locally-made pistols. He said that the command focused its recovery mainly on prohibited firearms with other weapons that fall within the category of what the criminal laws had criminalise, adding that there is a standing task force which is still working to enforce the directive.